i5.las2peer.logging

Class NodeObserver

  • java.lang.Object
    • i5.las2peer.logging.NodeObserver
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MonitoringObserver, NodeStreamLogger

    public abstract class NodeObserver
extends java.lang.Object
    The NodeObserver is an abstract class providing all necessary methods to log all interesting node events for a Node (mainly PastryNodeImpl).

      • getNodeRepresentation

        protected java.lang.String getNodeRepresentation(java.lang.Object node)
        Derive a String representation for a node from the given identifier object. The type of the object depends on the setting of the current node. Tries to specify an ip address and a port for an actual p2p node (PastryNodeImpl or NodeHandle).
        Parameters:
        node -
        Returns:
        string representation for the given node object

      • log

        protected void log(NodeObserver.Event event,
                   java.lang.Object sourceNode,
                   java.lang.Long sourceAgentId,
                   java.lang.Object destinationNode,
                   java.lang.Long destinationAgentId,
                   java.lang.String remarks)
        Writes a log entry.
        Parameters:
        event - necessary
        sourceNode - an object representing some kind of node will be transferred to an node representation if possible (see getNodeRepresentation(java.lang.Object)) (can be null)
        sourceAgentId - the id of the source agent (can be null)
        destinationNode - (can be null)
        destinationAgentId - (can be null)
        remarks - (can be null)

      • writeLog

        protected abstract void writeLog(java.lang.Long timestamp,
                                 NodeObserver.Event event,
                                 java.lang.String sourceNode,
                                 java.lang.Long sourceAgentId,
                                 java.lang.String destinationNode,
                                 java.lang.Long destinationAgentId,
                                 java.lang.String remarks)
        This method has to be implemented by any (non abstract) deriving class. Each call represents one event to log by this observer. All parameters except the time stamp and the event may be null.
        Parameters:
        timestamp - UNIX time stamp of the event
        event - the event to log
        sourceNode - a source (p2p) node of the event (e.g. message sender)
        sourceAgentId - a source (las2peer) agent of the event (e.g. message sender)
        destinationNode - a destination (p2p) node for the event (e.g. message receiver)
        destinationAgentId - a destination (las2peer) agent of the event (e.g. message receiver)
        remarks - (optional) additional remarks
